Sunday 6th July 2014 ITV4
7pm to 8pm Highlights

Highlights from the second of the two Yorkshire stages - 198km from York to Sheffield, passing through the hilly terrain of the Peak District. With 3,400m of climbing, the stage has been heralded as a British version of the classic Liege-Bastogne-Liege stage, with the notorious climb of Holme Moss 50km from the finish. Presented by Gary Imlach, with guests Chris Boardman and David Millar, commentary by Phil Liggett and Paul Sherwen, and reporter Ned Boulting.
